<br>
As a level 60 Paladin with a weapon that should be far better than the hammer (Windblade, 50 damage 44 delay and has a damage bonus of 37 at level 60), I do 27.77 DPS (yes, this is a parsed figure) against low dark blue experience MoBs, going to around 40-45 DPS when grouped with the best ATK buffs possible (places me at max haste and ~1250-1300 ATK) in actual experience zones (see: Planar). And by the way, I miss at least as often as I hit too--thanks, sucky skill caps. <br>
<br>
Now watch a Cleric with Speed of Vallon and Boon. Heck, you're a 65 Cleric. Get a SoV and Boon. A Focus too if you don't need the mana regen from BAoTR/Armor of the Zealot. I never said that the hammer itself did much DPS, I'd estimate the best any Cleric sees with those 1hers is around 10 DPS from melee hits. However, with those exact buffs I mentioned (minus Focus), I have seriously watched a 62 (or was it 63?) Cleric smacking away with a swing every ~1.2 seconds and proccing 2 out of 3 swings. 66% haste (no haste item) and max dex. There wasn't such thing as being able to see other non melee damage then, but watching more recently the average damage per proc of a Cleric proccing his hammer in Plane of Valor on Malosini'd (or whatever the level 57 or 58 version is called) MoBs, I'd have to say the previously mentioned buffed Cleric was doing around 45 DPS just on procs, probably another 5-6 with pure melee damage.<br>
<br>
<br>
Again I'll say... leave my freaking melee alone. I wouldn't mind being outDPS'd by Clerics if they used spells to do it, but as a melee being outdone at his own game by a WIS-Caster, I'm annoyed. True enough that I tank better, but that's my only advantage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pneumaticdryll>PneumaticDryll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Xev Pecking Order:<br>
