<br>
So what's the deal now?<br>
<br>
Well i'm a cleric, and I think these hammers are shit.  EQ is based up D&amp;D, and in D&amp;D Clerics can melee and in every other roleplaying game Clerics can melee, but they can't in EQ.<br>
<br>
To give the Cleric a meens of self defence against greens and indeed the meens to deliver a little extra damage to the group Sony decide to give us these hammers (but only once we reach 56th), therefor completely standardising the cleric overnight... Either you have your summoned hammer loaded, or your epic.<br>
<br>
There was a time when I was proud of the individuallity of my cleric, but overnight we all became gimpy clones.<br>
<br>
Yes at the very top end there are now clerics with better drop weapons, but really the problem with cleric melee'ing was not the weapons.  I had a 39/44 before PoP came along, it was a fine weapon with tons of stats and resists... it's now redundant.<br>
<br>
What clerics needed was an improvement to their melee ability, either to be granted the level damage bonus or to be given double attack - or perhaps both, just enough extra melee'ing ability so that a cleric with a melee specific weapon could actually act in a hybrid role on ocassion.<br>
<br>
I hate the bloody hammer, it's got a crap graphic and every other 56+ cleric in Everquest looks exactly the bloody same.<br>
<br>
They could at least have changed the graphics for the later level versions of it.<br>
<br>
Oh and Paladins should get better heals, if you cant get a cleric what do you seak?  Answer: Druid/Shaman.  Paladin should be part of that list too, they are gimp melee's and gimp healers but that really should not be the case.<br>
<br>
<br>
