<br>
<br>
I understand your point. I just don't agree with it, especially with weapons like windblades readily available. It's a ToV quality weapon that you used to have to raid to get. It gives people who don't or can't raid a viable option to DPS. <br>
<br>
It's not guaranteed to give you all the DPS in the world but when you start seeing a higher ATK rating and gain a few more levels you will notice a boost in DPS. I've been exactly where you're at right now myself so I do understand where you're coming from. When you start breaking 1250-1300ATK regularly at 65 with that sucker you'll be quite surprised!<br>
<br>
Clerics won't ever take your spot in a group since you're first and foremost a tank not a DPS class. Anything we add is just icing on the cake. Just like a cleric's main job is healing, buffing and any DPS they can add is just more icing on the cake as well.<br>
You're also tanking when parsing which does cut your DPS by a decent bit. Have a cleric tank the same mobs and try to do that much DPS. They won't, because they'll be dead which cuts their DPS quite drastically.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure if you're a raider or not. But I will say the 64 hammer is the end of the line on cleric DPS untill they get a drop from RZ. If you're a raider you'll see twice that DPS well before the cleric even has a shot at that. If not, the windblade will do it with some more ATK rating.<br>
